Struggling to debug SAP errors? You’re probably ignoring this underrated TCode…

There’s one transaction code every SAP consultant must know:
SLG1 - Analyse Application Log.

Most skip it.
The smart ones? They swear by it.

Here’s why:
↳ It helps you trace exactly what went wrong - with timestamps.
 ↳ You can filter by user, transaction code, and program.
 ↳ Want to check logs from background jobs or batch inputs? Done.
 ↳ Need to debug an error even after the user is long gone? No problem.
 ↳ It even lets you view logs from archived data!

Real-time use case?
 That nasty PO error your user reported 3 days back?
 Run SLG1 → Filter by user & time → Boom! The exact log is right there.

Perfect for:
 ✅ Functional consultants
 ✅ Support teams
 ✅ Audits & compliance checks

Don’t just react to issues.
 Trace. Solve. Document. Repeat.

Next time you're stuck in the dark,
 SLG1 is your flashlight.
